de.lambeck.pned.util

Interface ILIFOStack<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the Type of the elements
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IDataModelStack, IGuiModelStack
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DataModelStack, GuiModelStack

    public interface ILIFOStack<T>
    This interface allows hiding the implementation of Stack and exposing only the intended role (LIFO).

    Note: Stack has two problems:
    1. It is NOT an interface but a concrete class which means that we are bound to its implementation and not flexible.

    2. It extends Vector and this exposes methods which can insert elements to and get elements from specific positions. This means that a Stack can do more than a (LIFO) stack should be able to do.

    http://openbook.rheinwerk-verlag.de/javainsel9/javainsel_13_006.htm#mj0c9a4bc09c3ca7bb4407a33d4270d2b4
    Author:
    Thomas Lambeck, 4128320
